.TH "timeout_store" 9 "timeout_store" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
timeout_store \- set number of seconds to wait for firmware
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" timeout_store
.BI "(struct class *class "  ","
.BI "struct class_attribute *attr "  ","
.BI "const char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "class" 12
device class pointer
.IP "attr" 12
device attribute pointer
.IP "buf" 12
buffer to scan for timeout value
.IP "count" 12
number of bytes in \fIbuf\fP

Sets the number of seconds to wait for the firmware.  Once
this expires an error will be returned to the driver and no
firmware will be provided.
.SH "NOTE"
zero means 'wait forever'.
